<TEXT>
<P>
As weekly viewers of "Murphy Brown" (we haven't missed an episode), we want to 
express our thanks to the producers and writers for having Fred Travalena as 
the guest star on the Oct. 30 show. His portrayal of Don Sarasota, the absolute 
worst lounge performer, was a classic. The prime-time exposure given Travalena 
was long overdue. 
</P>
<P>
Charles and Inez Scott, Ventura 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA112689-0006 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 139802 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 26, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
