<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: COSTNER'S LAST STAND? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Pat H. Broeske 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Meanwhile, Columbia's "Revenge" -- which wrapped last Dec. 14, also with 
Costner starring -- isn't due out until February. The violence-laden love 
triangle, directed by Tony Scott and set in Mexico, has been in post-production 
for months . . . and months. 
</P>
<P>
"There are absolutely no problems," said a rep for producer Ray Stark. "It's 
just going through the traditional editing process." Pat H. Broeske 
</P>
</TEXT>
