A CHINA WATCHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So Orville Schell now realizes that he has been somewhat mistaken about the 
government of China ("The Re-Education of a China Watcher," by Jacques Leslie, 
Oct. 15). Hasn't he ever heard of the large-scale executions that took place 
there in the 1950s? What about the ongoing genocide against the Tibetans that 
has recently intensified? 
</P>
<P>
May we be protected from these naive, starry-eyed "China experts." Their 
misinformation is partly responsible for the continual misery of the Chinese 
people and our own befuddlement and inaction over events in China. 
</P>
