</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Smith states that Mozart would love his new programming. Mozart, when playing, 
would not abide a cough from an audience member. What makes Mr. Smith think 
that he would appreciate hearing his works truncated or sandwiched between 
jazz? 
</P>
<P>
