<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: YOUTH, 17, HITS CAR; ELDERLY WOMAN DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 68-year-old Lancaster woman died Saturday after her car was hit while she 
attempted a U-turn on L Street just west of the Sierra Highway in the Antelope 
Valley, the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department said. 
</P>
<P>
Her car was hit on the driver's side by a vehicle driven by a 17-year-old 
Lancaster youth. The victim's name was withheld pending notification of 
relatives, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The woman was taken to Antelope Valley Medical Center where she was pronounced 
dead from internal injuries, authorities said. 
</P>
