<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
* MARCH TO YOUR OWN BEAT: From star-studded tradition to offbeat kookiness, 
three parades planned for today should offer a little something for everyone. 
The 58th Annual Hollywood Christmas Parade led by Grand Marshal Sammy Davis Jr. 
kicks off at 6 p.m. at Van Ness Avenue and Sunset Boulevard. The 14th 
Occasional Doo-Dah Parade, a spoof of the Tournament of Roses, will take over 
Pasadena's streets from noon to 2 p.m. And the East Los Angeles Parade will run 
from 1 p.m. to 6 p.m. along Whittier and Atlantic boulevards. 
</P>
<P>
* CRUISE WITH SANTA: A double-decker bus, provided by the Hollywood Chamber of 
Commerce, will carry Santa Claus, a choir and a different high school band 
along Hollywood Boulevard every night for the next 19 days starting Monday. 
</P>
<P>
* SATAN SLEUTHS: Parents who want to ban a textbook because they believe it 
contains satanic material will present their grievances to officials of the 
East Whittier School District on Monday at 7 p.m. at East Whittier Middle 
School. 
</P>
<P>
* STRANGE MACHINATIONS: Engineering students at Caltech will compete Thursday 
to see who can build the best ping-pong-ball-collecting machine from a bag of 
assorted springs, plexiglass, tubing and electric motors provided by their 
instructor. The 4th Annual Caltech Engineering Design Contest gets underway at 
2 p.m. in the Baxter Lecture Hall in Pasadena. 
</P>
</TEXT>
