<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOLERANCE, DIVERSITY IN NEWPORT-MESA SCHOOLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding sex education in the Newport-Mesa school district, Bonnie O'Neil 
states that the curriculum should be chosen by "selected" parents and school 
personnel. Who will select the "selected" parents and by what and whose 
criteria? Will they be selected so that they ensure the students are presented 
with incomplete, inaccurate information that will ill prepare them to make 
life's difficult choices in this ever more complicated world? 
</P>
<P>
High school age students are not gullible little children whose behavior and 
values can be twisted any which way. If they are taught the "right" values at 
home then Ms. O'Neil need have no fear they will misuse the complete, accurate 
information they receive in a sex education class. 
</P>
<P>
JEAN WINTERFELT 
</P>
<P>
Newport Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
