<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIGERIA CHARGES 21 STUDENTS WITH ARSON IN PROTESTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAGOS, Nigeria 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The government has charged 21 students with arson in connection with a series 
of fires set during nationwide student protests in May. 
</P>
<P>
The students had been detained without charge since the protests, which left 43 
people dead. 
</P>
<P>
The 21 defendants, who were charged last week, pleaded innocent and were 
granted bail. They each could face seven years in prison if convicted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
