<HEADLINE>
<P>
RELIGIOUS BLACKMAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Soon our country will be celebrating the anniversary of the signing of the Bill 
of Rights of our Constitution. 
</P>
<P>
The Catholic bishops are a forceful political lobby with a tremendous economic 
base, thus violating the constitutional separation of church and state. Should 
they be tax exempt if they continue to participate in political action? 
</P>
<P>
Political candidates are representatives of their constituents and should vote 
accordingly. Otherwise, those of us who do pay taxes are taxed without 
representation. 
</P>
<P>
Thank you, Lucy Killea, for your firm stand against tyranny. You have our 
votes! 
</P>
<P>
JANE and RICHARD SPEAKER 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
