<HEADLINE>
<P>
POST OFFICE KUDOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There have been a number of recent articles concerning the U.S. Postal Service 
here in San Diego. Many of us in the mailing industry strongly disagree with 
the extremely negative comments in these articles and some of the comments 
attributed to Rep. Jim Bates. 
</P>
<P>
As co-chair of the San Diego Postal Customer Council, president of the San 
Diego Direct Marketing Club, and the owner of one of San Diego's largest 
direct-mail production companies, I think Margaret Sellers is an excellent 
postmaster. She is responsible for over 11,000 employees, almost 300 facilities 
and an annual budget in excess of $450 million. She has the task of managing 
these responsibilities as a government agency and a competitive business. While 
trying to provide top-notch service, Postmaster Sellers has to deal with 
constraints imposed on the Postal Service from Washington. 
</P>
<P>
Many of my employees and I have had a great deal of contact with postal 
employees at all levels. While there is always room for improvement, our 
positive experiences with the Post Office far out weigh the negative. 
</P>
<P>
RAYMOND G. ELLIS 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
