<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTORCYCLE CRASH KILLS CORPSMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A U.S. Navy corpsman was killed Friday after his motorcycle plowed into a 
stalled car on California 94, California Highway Patrol officers said. 
</P>
<P>
James L. Giles, 28, of Julian, was pronounced dead at 5 p.m. at UC San Diego 
Medical Center, about an hour after the collision on State 94 west of 
Interstate 805, San Diego County coroner's deputy Dan Matticks said Saturday. 
Giles, a corpsman stationed at the North Island Naval Air Station, died of 
internal injuries, Matticks said. 
</P>
<P>
Giles was riding his motorcycle east at about 55 m.p.h. when he struck a 1984 
Ford Bronco that had stalled ahead of him, CHP officers said. Hanna Abusalem, 
34, of La Mesa, the driver of the Bronco, was trying to re-start the car when 
Giles slammed into it from behind, officers said. 
</P>
