<HEADLINE>
<P>
NORTHRIDGE WOMEN FALL TO STANISLAUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kirsten Dumford scored 19 points and pulled down 11 rebounds to lead Cal State 
Stanislaus to a 91-69 win over visiting Cal State Northridge Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge's Denna Mulverhill led the Lady Matadors with 13 points. Bridgette 
Ealy and Julie Arlotto added 11 and 10 points, respectively, and both had seven 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Lisa Minturn of Stanislaus led all scorers with 22 points. 
</P>
<P>
Stanislaus (1-3) raced to an early 16-point advantage, but Northridge (1-3) 
trimmed it to three with less than two minutes remaining in the half. 
</P>
<P>
However, the Lady Matadors could get no closer as Stanislaus exploded for eight 
unanswered points to take an 11-point lead at the intermission. 
</P>
<P>
Dumford hit on five of seven three-point attempts for Stanislaus. 
</P>
