<HEADLINE>
<P>
POMONA RABBI WHO AIDED SOVIET JEWS URGES THE U.S. TO ADMIT MORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE WARD, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
POMONA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On the top of a bookshelf in the office of Rabbi Earl Kaplan at Temple Beth 
Israel sits an old Russian encyclopedia that has made a journey to freedom. 
</P>
<P>
The yellowed volume, about 70 years old, was given to Kaplan last month in 
