an ideal opportunity for the leaders to "create some kind of freedom-of-choice 
time period -- three months, six months or whatever -- so that anybody who 
wants to go from East to West or West to East can do it. Then, when the time 
period is over, that's it. You've made your decision, and there are no more 
problems and no more pressure." 
</P>
<P>
But if that sort of agreement is beyond reach, Kaplan said, then President Bush 
should raise the immigration quota. 
</P>
<P>
Kaplan said the United States also should be doing more to help Jews and 
members of the Bahai faith who have fled from Iran. He said he met a community 
of 500 Jews in Vienna who are living there after escaping from Iran. 
</P>
<P>
The rabbi said he is maintaining contact with Ambassador Melady and Rep. David 
Dreier (R-La Verne), who heads the Republican Task Force on Foreign Policy, to 
urge them to influence Administration policies to help refugees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
