<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.V. GIRLS WIN CROSS-COUNTRY TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRENT GOODRICH, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FRESNO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Winning the CIF State Division I cross-country title should be old hat for 
Palos Verdes High Coach Joe Kelly by now, but his latest crown could be the 
most satisfying. 
</P>
<P>
"This is without a doubt the best I've ever seen a Palos Verdes girls team 
run," Kelly said. 
</P>
<P>
The Sea King girls exploited their closely bunched running to nip favored 
Agoura by seven points, 68-75, and capture the school's third consecutive state 
team title Saturday at Woodward Park. 
</P>
<P>
Palos Verdes placed five runners in the top 20 of the team competition to 
offset the championship run of Agoura's Deena Drossin who won the individual 
title in 17 minutes, 27 seconds on the hilly, 5,000 meter course. 
</P>
<P>
In the Division I boys race, three South Bay runners placed in the top 12. 
Torrance Junior Israel Pose finished eighth overall in 15:30, a personal best 
for 5,000 meters. 
</P>
<P>
Greg Gonzalez also contributed to this story. 
</P>
</TEXT>
