<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHNEIDER IS SLALOM WINNER DESPITE FALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARK CITY, Utah 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Defending World Cup ski champion Vreni Schneider of Switzerland, who fell on 
her first run of the season, turned in two flawless runs to win the women's 
slalom Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Schneider, coming off the best season in the history of the World Cup tour with 
14 victories last year, negotiated the 427-meter course in 47.77 seconds on her 
first run and in 46.88 on her second for a total of 1:34.65. 
</P>
<P>
She easily beat Monika Maierhofer of Austria, who was timed in 48.26 on her 
first run and 47.71 on her second for a total of 1:35.97. 
</P>
<P>
Schneider, in her season debut Friday, fell in her first giant slalom run. 
</P>
</TEXT>
