<HEADLINE>
<P>
BYU EARNS RETURN TRIP TO SAN DIEGO, 48-27; 
</P>
<P>
COUGARS: DETMER ACCOUNTS FOR FIVE TOUCHDOWNS TO HELP CLINCH WAC TITLE AND A 
SPOT IN THE HOLIDAY BOWL. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brigham Young University clinched the Western Athletic Conference title and 
earned its first Holiday Bowl berth since its 1984 national championship by 
defeating San Diego State, 48-27, Saturday night as Ty Detmer passed for 327 
yards and accounted for five touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
The No. 21-ranked Cougars (10-2 overall, 7-1 in the WAC) will return to San 
Diego Jack Murphy Stadium to play No. 22 Penn State in the Holiday Bowl on Dec. 
29. Penn State beat Pitt, 16-13, Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Detmer, who passed for three touchdowns and ran for two, completed 23 of 33 
passes and finished the season with 4,560 yards, falling just short of the 
major-college record of 4,571 by BYU's Jim McMahon in 1980. 
</P>
<P>
The Cougars' Stacey Corley rushed seven times for 121 yards, including runs of 
57 and 49 yards. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State (6-5-1, 4-3) finished with its first winning record in three 
years. 
</P>
<P>
Aztec quarterback Dan McGwire missed much of the first half due to a back 
bruise on the Aztecs' first possession but returned to complete 14 of 21 passes 
for 215 yards and a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
The Aztecs trailed, 35-14, in the third quarter before closing to 35-24 on a 
32-yard pass from McGwire to Tony Nettles and a 46-yard field goal by Andy 
Trakas. 
</P>
<P>
But Detmer put the Cougars comfortably ahead again with a one-yard touchdown 
run late in the quarter after Dave Porter recovered a fumble by Monty Gilbreath 
on a punt return at the Aztecs' 19. 
</P>
<P>
In the fourth quarter, Trakas added a 38-yard field goal and BYU's Fred 
Whittingham scored on a 34-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
The Cougars trailed, 14-13, after one quarter but scored 22 points in the 
second quarter for a 35-14 halftime lead. Jeff Frandsen put BYU ahead, 21-14, 
early in the second quarter when he caught a 27-yard pass from Detmer, his 
second touchdown reception. 
</P>
<P>
The Cougars added two touchdowns in the final 2:33 of the half when Matt 
Bellini scored on a three-yard run and Andy Boyce made a diving catch of 
Detmer's nine-yard scoring pass with 18 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
Curtis Butts and Ron Slack scored on short runs for San Diego State in the 
first quarter. Frandsen scored on a 67-yard pass play, and Detmer scrambled 12 
yards for BYU's touchdowns in the first quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, BYU's Andy Boyce gets catches pass in front of Clark Moses of San Diego 
St. United Press International 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
