<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE LOOKING FOR HIT-AND-RUN DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COSTA MESA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police are seeking the public's help in finding a hit-and-run driver who 
collided with a motorcyclist Wednesday at 5:45 p.m. at the corner of Harbor 
Boulevard and Mesa Verde Drive East. 
</P>
<P>
The suspect, described by witnesses as a 20- to 25-year-old woman with blond 
hair, was driving a late 1970s blue Toyota Celica hatchback, said traffic 
investigator Steve Rautus. The woman reportedly made an unsafe lane change in 
front of a motorcycle, causing it to rear-end the car, lose control and crash. 
The victim, Rick Muller, 31 of Santa Ana, remains in stable condition at United 
Western Medical Center-Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the driver stopped a half block from the accident, observed the 
scene and then fled. Witnesses said the numbers of the license plate are 378 
and the letters resemble HPN. Rautus said there might have been rear-end damage 
to the car. 
</P>
<P>
Anyone with information about the driver should call Rautus or investigator 
Floyd Waldon at (714) 754-5367. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
TRAFFIC ACCIDENTS -- ORANGE COUNTY; HIT AND RUN DRIVERS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
